zhoneMasterAgentMIB.description: The MIB module to describe the Zhone specific implementation of the Master Agent. These fields go beyond those defined in RFC1907 (snmp).

maRequestPort.name: maRequestPort
maRequestPort.description: The IP Port number that should be used by the SNMP manager when sending/receiving messages. This will not be used in the initial release. The default value for this field is 161.

maTrapPort.name: maTrapPort
maTrapPort.description: The IP port number that should be used when sending traps to any Fault Manager Service.

maPerfSaRequests.name: maPerfSaRequests
maPerfSaRequests.description: Number of requests sent by the Master Agent to any Sub-Agent in the device. In a single SNMP PDU, multiple Sub-Agents may be required to process the individual VarBinds. This count will increment for each of these individual messages and therefore is not a 1:1 relationship with the number of SNMP PDU's requiring Sub-Agent Processing.

maPerfSaResponses.name: maPerfSaResponses
maPerfSaResponses.description: Number of Sub-Agent responses to the requests issued. Unless there are internal errors, this should match the maSARequestCount

maPerfSnmpErrors.name: maPerfSnmpErrors
maPerfSnmpErrors.description: The number of Master-Agent errors detected on SNMP PDU's received. Examples are parsing errors but does not include such items as community table invalid and noSuchInstance cases.

maPerfSaTimeouts.name: maPerfSaTimeouts
maPerfSaTimeouts.description: The number of timeouts that have occurred due to a lack of response from a sub-agent to a request.
